{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Score Unlike BERTScore which relies on embedding-based similarity matching using pretrained text encoders, BARTScore (Yuan et al., 2021) evaluates text generation based on the likelihood under a pre-trained BART model (Lewis et al., 2020), making it context-aware and fluent-focused.",
    "Score = m t=1 ω t log p(y t |y <t, x, θ), here the weight w t can be initialized by inverse document frequencies (IDF).",
    "Lebron et al. (2022) introduced BERTHA, a BERT-based model equipped with a scoring head trained on human evaluations of machine-generated captions to enhance alignment with human judgment.",
    "The model is optimized to maximize the Pearson correlation coefficient with human assessments, ensuring a more accurate and human-aligned evaluation of generated captions.",
    "Metrics based on N-gram overlap and semantic relevance are text-only evaluation methods."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
